climbs.name: Cheap Like Nude Pantyhose and White Sandals

content.description: Stand start in the middle of the south face. Utilizing crimps and one good side pull, make your way to the top.
content.protection: Pads and a spotter. The landing has one rock underneath but it is easily covered.
content.location: The down climb is located on the west face.

climbs.name: You Will Have Taylor Doose to Kick Around Again

content.description: Squat start on the left side of the main (south) face. Move up the arete using delicate feet and positive hands.
content.location: There is a slide down, down climb on the west side of the boulder.

content.description: Sit start on the right side of the east corner of the boulder. Move up the "lip" and to the arete and move upward using crimps and slopers and pinches (on the arete).
content.location: There is a down climb on the west side of the boulder. Reference picture for route/problem details.

content.description: Squat start on the right side of the south face utilizing a good hold on the arete and a left hand crimp. Avoid the obvious good food hold on the right for a smaller left foot and move upward on the arete.
content.protection: Pads and a spotter but the landing is good.
content.location: Located in the center of the south face. Down climb on the west side of the boulder.
